Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.32,0:00:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know where we were until I realized we were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.32,0:01:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. We have 10 people that are from Korea that are in the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.93,0:01:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could please stand up. Stand up for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.93,0:01:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They came all the way from Korea to be with us today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.93,0:01:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are the 10 people? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.67,0:01:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We have 10 people from Korea that are here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.06,0:01:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.06,0:01:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.87,0:01:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We appreciate you traveling such a long way.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.09,0:01:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We also have a lot of people here from Canada.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.09,0:01:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are the Canadians?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.09,0:01:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.57,0:01:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to acknowledge them because they have come from such a long way.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.57,0:01:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have a terrific following in Korea.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.57,0:02:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And these people, you know, we really appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.57,0:02:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They were one of the first people that David and I did a seminar for, was in Korea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.58,0:02:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And we went all the way over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.58,0:02:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That was, I think it was 1999.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.77,0:02:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1999, we started it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.77,0:02:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Dr. Moon has an ashram there who is continuing with our teachings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.77,0:02:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And she is translating all the work into Korean for those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.77,0:02:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just wanted to acknowledge you and thank you so much for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.77,0:02:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here from Dubai today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.77,0:02:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Dubai. Anybody here from Dubai?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.90,0:02:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.68,0:02:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have our Dubai people here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.58,0:02:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Dubai-ers?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.83,0:02:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I think she's coming till October, honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.83,0:02:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a couple of people that come over from Dubai also.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.83,0:02:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think they said they were coming to the October lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.83,0:02:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Or India. Or India.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.83,0:02:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,How about our Indian people?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.83,0:03:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Is anyone here from India?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.83,0:03:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Come on. Stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.83,0:03:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Australia. Australia, India.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.84,0:03:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.86,0:03:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just wanted to acknowledge everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.86,0:03:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I could have everyone standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.62,0:03:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there's going to be no recording of the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.62,0:03:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if any of you are doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.62,0:03:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But we cannot have you record the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.62,0:03:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all copyrighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.62,0:03:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And so if any of you are recording it, we'd ask you to please refrain from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.62,0:03:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.62,0:03:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. We'll resume.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.93,0:03:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We have exactly one hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.66,0:03:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.96,0:04:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We got up to number 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.96,0:04:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We better move along.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.99,0:04:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think we're going to have to go back to the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.99,0:04:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to have to go back to the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.99,0:04:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's go back to the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.09,0:04:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think you're going to have to go back to the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.09,0:04:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you're going to have to go back to the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.18,0:04:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.18,0:04:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.18,0:04:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So the question is, how do you evaluate wisdom over being right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.18,0:04:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not necessary to be right unless you're a – you feel that you have to fight for your image.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.45,0:04:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the image is that you have to be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.45,0:04:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's of greater value to be understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.45,0:04:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing that people ignore in our current society,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.45,0:04:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think that's something that we all need to be aware of,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.62,0:04:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you don't have to solve everything all by yourself without discussing it with anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.62,0:04:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody should have somebody, a mentor, that they look up to, that they respect,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.81,0:04:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,can be just a very good friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.17,0:04:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But instead of keeping everything to yourself and sweating it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.36,0:05:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you can talk to people that you respect because you get feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.22,0:05:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a reason for it other than just the practicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.22,0:05:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The practicality is you don't get so egotistic about whatever your conclusion is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.35,0:05:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you didn't conclude to do that all by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.35,0:05:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You discussed it with a friend, and the two of you decided that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.44,0:05:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if the two of you decided that, then you don't say,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.44,0:05:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I'm the one that picked the winning ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.44,0:05:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.44,0:05:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I picked the winning ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.37,0:05:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you discuss the winning ticket to buy with somebody else,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.37,0:05:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a shared, joint decision,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.39,0:05:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and that, you know, protects you from egotistical inflation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.39,0:05:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're looking for ways to transcend the ego and allow the spirit to take over,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.39,0:05:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is one of the ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.56,0:06:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In all my years in psychiatry and psychoanalysis,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.00,0:06:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it was another rule to always have a colleague to discuss things with,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.23,0:06:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,even though I'd had 50 years' experience as a psychiatrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.23,0:06:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,One time I had, for many years, the largest practice in the entire United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.23,0:06:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I still had somebody that I saw periodically to discuss things with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.25,0:06:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get feedback from other people, and they have other ways of looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.57,0:06:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And so sometimes my counsel would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.57,0:06:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,well, that sounds good, but you could look at it this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.57,0:06:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I hadn't thought of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.74,0:06:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's good to have a confessor,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.74,0:06:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,confessor, a counselor, a therapist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.74,0:06:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody should have a psychotherapist, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.22,0:06:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anybody that doesn't need a psychotherapist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.22,0:07:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,People who think they don't need a therapist are the most gone of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.66,0:07:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I can do it on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.56,0:07:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.10,0:07:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a good spouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.10,0:07:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Have somebody that you can confide in,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.10,0:07:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,share in reaching decisions,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.10,0:07:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and it serves your highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.16,0:07:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,To always have somebody to share with serves your highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.16,0:07:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.62,0:07:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I got you, babe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.93,0:07:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.93,0:07:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, it was wise counsel that led to me sharing things with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.50,0:07:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.30,0:08:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.30,0:08:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.35,0:08:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk with Susie and then make up your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.76,0:08:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.22,0:08:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.22,0:08:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that you influence others by what you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.22,0:08:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,not just by what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.22,0:08:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We subtly or constantly influencing actually all of mankind by what we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.81,0:08:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you are is more important than what you do
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.81,0:08:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because what you are radiates out an energy that influences everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.81,0:08:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What you are, what you have become is more powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.46,0:08:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,People can say, what can I do to help mankind?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.46,0:08:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And I tell them, become the most loving, evolved person that you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.61,0:08:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Love all of life and all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.61,0:08:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Be respectful of nature and beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.61,0:08:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Esteem beauty and nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.61,0:09:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that you influence others by what you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.96,0:09:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,not what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.96,0:09:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So this group here right now is influencing mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.96,0:09:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This group is influencing mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.14,0:09:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not doing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.14,0:09:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have any flags to wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.14,0:09:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have any slogans.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.14,0:09:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not shouting into the TV reporter's microphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.14,0:09:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This group right here is influencing all of mankind right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.88,0:09:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.75,0:09:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.75,0:09:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You radiate out an energy into the field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.75,0:09:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which influences everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.77,0:09:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So that the best thing you can do for the world
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.10,0:09:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is to sit down and shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.01,0:09:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind thoughts that you have towards others,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.01,0:10:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the kindly thoughts, the kindly intention that you have towards others,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.11,0:10:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to influence all of mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.77,0:10:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole field of consciousness of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.20,0:10:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that you are influencing others right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.20,0:10:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Not by what you say, but what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.38,0:10:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why I am not an enthusiast of activism.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.63,0:10:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Activism, everybody, you know, they get on TV
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.76,0:10:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and they have a thing around their thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.76,0:10:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They're a blogger activist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.76,0:10:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I salute all blogger activists.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.16,0:10:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my blogger activist salute.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.98,0:10:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I salute you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.74,0:10:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They actually get on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.19,0:10:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And they're being interviewed by the chair of the thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.19,0:11:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what they're, underneath it says blogger activist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.82,0:11:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask them, what have they blogged lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.82,0:11:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Screw you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.82,0:11:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.82,0:11:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.38,0:11:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoid activism and pedantry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.38,0:11:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, well, isn't that the American way?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.38,0:11:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the American way of certain people in America at certain times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.38,0:11:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.38,0:11:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you choose spirituality as a lifestyle,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.38,0:11:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you can give up the activist signs and the parades,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.38,0:11:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,most of which is egoistic display.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.41,0:11:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Most activism is egocentricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.41,0:11:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at me, how important I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.41,0:11:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And listen to me because what I have to say is so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.74,0:11:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not important to anybody except you, but anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.74,0:11:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good on active.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.74,0:12:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'll see on TV, you'll see it's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.74,0:12:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It says activist, blogger and activist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.74,0:12:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That was on this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.74,0:12:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I said a blogger activist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.74,0:12:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.74,0:12:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only 150 million of them in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.77,0:12:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Be grateful for your assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.83,0:12:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Be glad that you're. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.14,0:12:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,smart and good looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.88,0:12:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And that you're tolerant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.98,0:12:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And your biggest asset is that you have become interested
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.98,0:12:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in spiritual evolution and spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.98,0:12:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and serving God and your fellow man.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.98,0:12:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It is helpful to your ego to remind yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.52,0:12:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that mankind has survived millions of years without your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.52,0:12:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how mankind got along without me all these years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.29,0:13:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So intrinsic to spiritual evolution is humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.87,0:13:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, yours is the saddest story I've ever heard is a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.15,0:13:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can also add to it as another sentence,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.25,0:13:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind has survived without you so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.89,0:13:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That way you don't take yourself so seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.89,0:13:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Take yourself so seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.05,0:13:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,By doing these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.60,0:13:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you become your own best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.60,0:13:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Putting a little thing on your mirror that says
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.26,0:13:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,yours is the saddest story I've ever heard
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.26,0:13:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and mankind has survived all millions of years without you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.53,0:13:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you're already being your best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.53,0:13:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You're bringing your ego in. . .
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.09,0:13:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You're putting a leash on your ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.22,0:14:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,reminding yourself of the reality
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.44,0:14:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are of benefit to mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.44,0:14:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,To the degree that you radiate God's love.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.57,0:14:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The degree that you radiate love.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.65,0:14:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconditional love to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.65,0:14:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You are being your own best friend
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.29,0:14:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and you are doing everything you can to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.29,0:14:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is full of do-gooders.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.87,0:14:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And the history of do-gooders is rather catastrophic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.61,0:14:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always a do-gooder,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.86,0:14:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and they like politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.86,0:14:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They like to control other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.86,0:14:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That for your own good,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.86,0:14:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to reduce the so-and-so and peanut butter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.89,0:14:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They're after one thing or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.89,0:14:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Candy, peanut butter, booze, smoking,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.89,0:14:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, chewing tobacco and whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.89,0:14:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always a do-gooder
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.12,0:14:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,going to do something do-good for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.12,0:14:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Do-good for you, meaning control you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.12,0:14:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What they mean is they want to control you in a certain way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.12,0:15:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for your own health.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.82,0:15:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not let me worry about my health?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.82,0:15:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The longer I live, the more it costs the taxpayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.69,0:15:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want people to quit smoking, quit drinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.94,0:15:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and driving fast while they're blind drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.44,0:15:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an interesting book on do-gooders by Mona Chiron.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.47,0:15:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Real do-gooders.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to experience some of it in great detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.88,0:15:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,At one time I had the largest psychiatric practice
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.98,0:15:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States for many years
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.98,0:15:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and the greatest hospital practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.98,0:15:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was also in charge of many hospitals, state hospitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.04,0:15:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Where there was 3,000, 5,000, even up to 9,000 patients
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.04,0:15:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,all in a giant hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.04,0:15:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So the do-gooders came along and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.17,0:16:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,well, there is no such thing as mental illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.26,0:16:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just a myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.16,0:16:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the idiot who said that, but there he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.16,0:16:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I invite him to have one of them live with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.49,0:16:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see how long he thinks it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.49,0:16:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,After he burns down your house and stabs your wife to death
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.49,0:16:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and rapes your daughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.49,0:16:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll see whether it's a myth or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.49,0:16:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, do-gooders was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.58,0:16:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mental illness was a myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.58,0:16:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget the idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.58,0:16:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Some psychiatrist who really...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.61,0:16:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He's probably on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.61,0:16:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mean to say anything mean about this,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.61,0:16:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.63,0:16:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mental illness was just a myth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.63,0:16:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So they opened the doors of the state hospitals
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.63,0:16:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and let these poor victims out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.63,0:16:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, victimology pictured these poor souls
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.96,0:16:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as being the victims of the system,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.96,0:16:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the hospital was like incarcerating.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.96,0:16:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the reality was that these people were not capable
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.05,0:17:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of taking care of themselves on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.05,0:17:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, that's the main reason they're there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.05,0:17:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that they were mentally ill or emotionally ill,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.05,0:17:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but they frankly couldn't take care of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.05,0:17:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So they closed the doors of the state hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.05,0:17:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these people went out into the street,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.05,0:17:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and they became today's street people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.05,0:17:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The street people you see in any big city years back
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.05,0:17:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,were in a mental hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.59,0:17:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In the mental hospital, you got three good meals a day
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.59,0:17:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,balanced by dieticians.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.59,0:17:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You got free medical treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.66,0:17:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You got legal protection, medical protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.66,0:17:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You got all kinds of protection, and things were done for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.66,0:17:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You never...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.66,0:17:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How often do those people go to the dentist
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.66,0:17:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,laying on the street?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.66,0:17:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Their teeth fall out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.66,0:17:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In a mental hospital, you see the dentist, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.66,0:17:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Mona Shirin details that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.66,0:17:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, do-gooders always have something wonderful
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.66,0:17:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they think will be good for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.40,0:17:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Another thing that's wonderful is to let other people win.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.80,0:18:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting others win is very gratifying,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.80,0:18:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and it makes them very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.38,0:18:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So letting other people win arguments,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.38,0:18:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, you're right, honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.38,0:18:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right. You're right, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.70,0:18:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She does it with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.58,0:18:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She says, well, we'll do as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.58,0:18:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do as you say. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.09,0:18:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason we do is I say because I let her win
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.17,0:18:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,by saying, we'll do what you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.17,0:18:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That puts her on top.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.23,0:18:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I got to think of a way to count her
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.23,0:18:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to be on top of that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.00,0:18:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Beware of unintended consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.13,0:18:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is very well known in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.13,0:18:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You intend for a thing to go in a certain direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.13,0:18:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and there are other factors
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.13,0:18:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,involved that you're unaware of.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.13,0:19:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that in trying to develop compassion for people
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.56,0:19:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and their propensity to make grave errors,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.56,0:19:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the grave errors is the innocent child
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.56,0:19:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is present in everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.56,0:19:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So the innocent child in all of us reads
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.85,0:19:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,a book like Do-Gooders and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.85,0:19:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,let's go and save the mentally ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.85,0:19:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,They're being imprisoned against their will,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.85,0:19:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and mental illness is just a myth anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.85,0:19:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Who believes that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.98,0:19:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The innocent child is present in everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.14,0:19:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You could also call it the idiot child.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.61,0:19:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The child is innocent, innocent,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.19,0:19:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and is present in everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.28,0:19:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason you believe what you believe
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.60,0:19:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is because the innocent child in you believes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.60,0:19:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Within us is the child, the adult and the parent,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.60,0:19:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is a good designation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.70,0:20:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the child within you,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.70,0:20:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to believe the adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.70,0:20:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially the parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.93,0:20:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So the parent within you says,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.93,0:20:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I read it in the paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.93,0:20:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or I saw it on television,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.93,0:20:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or I read a good book on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.93,0:20:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's enough to impress the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.18,0:20:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The innocent child is present in everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.33,0:20:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Who makes the mistake when you screw up?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.65,0:20:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it that really screws up?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.65,0:20:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the innocent child.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.73,0:20:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're going to blame somebody,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.16,0:20:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who are you going to blame?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.19,0:20:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to blame the parent, the superego?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.19,0:20:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.19,0:20:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You tend to blame the adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.19,0:20:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but it wasn't the adult that fell for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.19,0:20:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the innocent child.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.19,0:20:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The innocent child, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.57,0:20:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is what's gullible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.57,0:20:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the political discussions
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.57,0:20:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that you hear so heatedly on Fox News and others
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.57,0:21:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is appealing to the innocent child and other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.57,0:21:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This one must know what they're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.57,0:21:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay, because they got this title.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.57,0:21:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the czar of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.57,0:21:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They must know what they're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.57,0:21:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The innocent child believes that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.78,0:21:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The government believes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.78,0:21:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The voters believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.03,0:21:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would even suspect the innocent child
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.03,0:21:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't know his ass from a hot rock?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.03,0:21:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,How can a czar not know his what from a hot rock?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.83,0:21:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't even pay his own income taxes yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.38,0:21:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.85,0:21:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you see things differently,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.85,0:21:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,it brings up the whole reframe and recontextualize.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.33,0:21:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What does a thing mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.66,0:21:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Means...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.00,0:22:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.00,0:22:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It means if you frame it this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.00,0:22:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the way it looks,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.00,0:22:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you frame it differently,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.00,0:22:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks different.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.03,0:22:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.03,0:22:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing you've changed is the frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.80,0:22:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If I take an idiot and he babbles idiocy,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.80,0:22:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, he's a dumb nut.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.08,0:22:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If I give him a title,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.08,0:22:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Congressman from someplace, rather,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.08,0:22:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I've recontextualized him,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.08,0:22:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and now he's a politician.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.08,0:22:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A minute ago, he was a dumb nut,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.08,0:22:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but now I've reframed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.23,0:22:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Critics are a dime a dozen,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.23,0:22:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,except that the majority of people calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.05,0:22:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you won't be disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.05,0:22:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Your peace will not be disturbed
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.05,0:22:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because your expectation of people
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.05,0:22:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is if they survive and are pleasant,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.05,0:22:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that in itself is fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.05,0:22:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that they're surviving
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.05,0:22:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and they still got a job
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.05,0:23:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or they're still taking care of the kids, whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.22,0:23:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the majority of people calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.22,0:23:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we showed that with the graph before.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.22,0:23:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So mankind is not anywhere near as evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.22,0:23:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,as you think it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.28,0:23:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of the criticism that we have of others,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.28,0:23:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,politics or anything else in our society,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.28,0:23:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is the expectation of a higher level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.28,0:23:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,than the people are capable of.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.45,0:23:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The majority of people cannot tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.44,0:23:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a shock?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.36,0:23:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.20,0:23:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.25,0:23:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.07,0:23:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.07,0:23:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.07,0:23:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that reframe your understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.13,0:23:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of the human condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.13,0:23:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The human mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.04,0:23:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,humanity, people,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.94,0:23:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,whole nations,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.94,0:24:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,whole civilizations
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.94,0:24:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,are unable to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.27,0:24:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Whole societies,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.27,0:24:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,whole civilizations,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.27,0:24:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,whole generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.27,0:24:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a whole generation of Germans
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.73,0:24:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,fired in World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.73,0:24:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mein Kampf.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.06,0:24:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions of people worshiping this guy
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.06,0:24:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,who's going to be the savior
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.06,0:24:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of right the wrongs of World War I
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.06,0:24:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.32,0:24:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Lead mankind to new,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.32,0:24:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a pure race and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.32,0:24:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You say,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.38,0:24:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,how can millions of people
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.38,0:24:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,follow a guy who calibrates about 170?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.81,0:24:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see in other countries right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.81,0:24:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,dictators around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.81,0:24:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all calibrate about 170.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.36,0:24:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You want a brain surgeon
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.36,0:24:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,who calibrates at 170?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.69,0:24:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even want a cook
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.69,0:24:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that calibrates at 170.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.82,0:25:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So we tailor our expectations of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.98,0:25:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We become more forgiving
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.98,0:25:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because we realize that error
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.98,0:25:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is due to ignorance,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.98,0:25:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's due to the child,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.98,0:25:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the inner child within oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.98,0:25:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can impress anyone's inner child,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.98,0:25:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what convinces people.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.98,0:25:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what the media do constantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.98,0:25:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They try to impress the inner child.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.98,0:25:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll give somebody a fantastic title,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.21,0:25:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Czar.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.21,0:25:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Czar.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.21,0:25:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The Czar of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.43,0:25:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.43,0:25:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the Czar must know something about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.43,0:25:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The Czar doesn't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.50,0:25:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Except the majority of people
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.54,0:25:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.83,0:25:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.83,0:25:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now those who are spiritually oriented,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.97,0:25:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,judge not lest ye be judged.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.97,0:25:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.97,0:25:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So that does not mean to go to sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.22,0:26:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and be unaware of reality
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.22,0:26:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and the essence of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.22,0:26:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But what does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.38,0:26:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What it means is
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.85,0:26:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,they realize that people cannot help themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.85,0:26:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because of their own inner limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.85,0:26:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, everyone is intrinsically innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.85,0:26:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If they could be better than they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.01,0:26:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,they would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.01,0:26:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,To say they could be better
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.77,0:26:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is a hypothetical egotism.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.77,0:26:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.20,0:26:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot be better than you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.20,0:26:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Judge not lest ye be judged.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.42,0:26:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.77,0:26:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.77,0:26:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the motives in whose eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.77,0:26:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,judge none.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.04,0:26:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean to be blind
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.55,0:26:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to the reality of what people are.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.55,0:26:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To recognize that somebody is a crook
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.72,0:26:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,who's on the take
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.72,0:27:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is merely a recognition of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.03,0:27:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's different than judgmentalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.03,0:27:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Judgmentalism says he shouldn't be that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.35,0:27:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if he could be different than he is,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.35,0:27:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,he would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.35,0:27:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All viewpoints are arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.05,0:27:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All viewpoints are arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.05,0:27:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.31,0:27:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they all represent a positionality
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.31,0:27:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and the result of framing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.31,0:27:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Looked at from this viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.31,0:27:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.31,0:27:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Looked at from this viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.31,0:27:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.34,0:27:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.34,0:27:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,all viewpoints are arbitrary
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.85,0:27:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.85,0:27:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you judge not.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.15,0:27:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.98,0:27:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that any judgment you can make
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.98,0:27:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,represents a viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.98,0:27:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and that viewpoint itself
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.98,0:27:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.01,0:27:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.01,0:27:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,saves us the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.01,0:27:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of getting into fixed
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.01,0:28:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,fixed positionalities of rigidity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.32,0:28:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A spiritually evolved person
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.32,0:28:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,avoids rigidity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.32,0:28:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't mean they have
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.32,0:28:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,they lose certainty about the reality
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.32,0:28:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as they have known it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.32,0:28:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's no longer an arbitrary position.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.54,0:28:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,There are lots of people
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.79,0:28:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,who don't believe in God
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.79,0:28:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and I understand them completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.79,0:28:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And they get on
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.96,0:28:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and they rant and rave
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.96,0:28:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're creative about the evil of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.96,0:28:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,religion and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.96,0:28:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Godness and all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.01,0:28:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I myself was a devout
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.01,0:28:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,atheist for 20 years or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.15,0:28:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I wasn't an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.15,0:28:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a non-believer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.44,0:28:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I was extremely religious,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.44,0:28:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,very religious.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.66,0:28:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And then,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.66,0:28:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,due to a very major inner psychic event,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.10,0:28:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I switched from being
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.77,0:28:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,very religious to the point of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.77,0:28:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,hyper-religiosity
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.91,0:28:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and instantly became an agnostic.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.51,0:29:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Became an atheist actually
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.51,0:29:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and later on an agnostic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.02,0:29:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I've told that before.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.02,0:29:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was walking through the woods one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.02,0:29:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I had a very religious upbringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.02,0:29:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a boat boy for the bishop.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.02,0:29:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was an acolyte.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.02,0:29:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I sang in the church choir.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.02,0:29:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a boy soloist at the cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.22,0:29:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was about as religious as you could get.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.22,0:29:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My family was religious.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.22,0:29:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And one day I was walking through the woods
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.45,0:29:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,not thinking about religion
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.30,0:29:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,or God or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.59,0:29:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden out of nowhere
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.59,0:29:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,arose
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.72,0:29:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,a vision of the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.54,0:29:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering of all of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.80,0:29:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.45,0:29:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.45,0:29:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly the curtain was pulled aside
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.45,0:29:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.79,0:29:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the enormity and gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.79,0:29:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of the suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.79,0:30:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.27,0:30:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that instant
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.27,0:30:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I became an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.66,0:30:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I can't believe in a God
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.46,0:30:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,who would allow that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.46,0:30:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So I blamed the suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.84,0:30:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.00,0:30:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,on God.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.82,0:30:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What I didn't realize
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.82,0:30:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that would have been revealed to me
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.82,0:30:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,was not divinity but the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.82,0:30:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What I was looking at
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.96,0:30:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is the profound destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.96,0:30:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and the massive agony and suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.05,0:30:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that the ego has brought
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.05,0:30:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,man over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.05,0:30:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is demonic,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.75,0:30:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the devil, whatever you want to call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.75,0:30:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is evil, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.04,0:30:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.84,0:30:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it took me a good 20 years
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.84,0:30:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to discover the mistake I had made.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.84,0:30:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't God
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.94,0:30:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,responsible for all that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.94,0:30:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but mankind himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.17,0:30:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Greediness is not taught by God.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.17,0:31:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.17,0:31:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the suffering of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.17,0:31:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is then brought about
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.17,0:31:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,by the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.97,0:31:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't even blame the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.97,0:31:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.97,0:31:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,innocence of the inner child
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.97,0:31:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that believes the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.38,0:31:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So man's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.74,0:31:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering then really arises
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.74,0:31:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,out of his lack of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.76,0:31:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.76,0:31:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ignorance that accompanies
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.76,0:31:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,being deaf, dumb, and blind
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.76,0:31:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,through the presence of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.76,0:31:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.76,0:31:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,God was reborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.30,0:31:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,God was happy about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.30,0:31:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez, Dave, thank God you made that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.30,0:31:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that the majority
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.30,0:31:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of people calibrate below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.30,0:31:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the source of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.30,0:31:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,man's suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.41,0:31:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All viewpoints are arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.53,0:31:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore we renew thankfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.53,0:31:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.59,0:31:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day we say
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.59,0:32:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,our Father who art in heaven
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.59,0:32:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,may we see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.75,0:32:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.75,0:32:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.91,0:32:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.91,0:32:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.91,0:32:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.91,0:32:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.91,0:32:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.91,0:32:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.91,0:32:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.91,0:32:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.20,0:32:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.20,0:32:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.20,0:32:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.20,0:32:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Alaska. Very impressive. I don't know. He's very impressive, his simplicity. All right. So we
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.04,0:32:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,renew our thankfulness and gratitude. And now a really, really liberating understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.11,0:32:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind, which you consider yourself, is not you. It's an it. The mind is what talks all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.48,0:33:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What talks is not the spirit, but the ego. The spirit doesn't talk. The mind is an it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.05,0:33:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not who you are. In the enlightened state, you realize you're not the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.51,0:33:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not the mind. You are something that goes beyond and encompasses both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.32,0:33:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is an it. It's not a you. So when you listen to the mind, you can refer to it as it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.29,0:33:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it thinking about taking this driveway home? Huh? That's what it is thinking. Not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.04,0:33:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The real I, the real I, the self with a capital S, is the presence of divinity within.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.75,0:33:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The radiance of consciousness itself, without which you wouldn't even know that you exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.32,0:34:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of all awareness is the self with a capital S, which is not different than
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.91,0:34:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.41,0:34:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness, then, is the radiance of divinity as all that exists. The radiance of all that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.19,0:34:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,exists. Out of consciousness arises the universe. Out of consciousness arises the universe and all
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.94,0:34:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that exists. The mind is an it, is not a you. And critics are a dime a dozen. People will say,
